                  <summary><p>The bundle contains two works attributed to <persName xml:lang="ta">Auvaiyār</persName>:
  <list rend="numbered">
  <item>the <title xml:lang="ta">Ātticūṭi</title> (complete)</item>
    <item>the <title xml:lang="ta">Koṉṟaivēntāṉ</title> (incomplete; first nine aphorisms only)</item>
  </list>
These works are often used for learning the Tamil alphabet as the aphorisms are ordered alphabetically and represent all the letters of the Tamil alphabet. The present manuscript, from <geogName>Pondicherry</geogName> (see U1b, <locus facs="15">f[6]r, c2, 3</locus>), might be a school exercise, as it contains mistakes apparently due to inexperience (e.g. confusion between the letters <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṉ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">ḷ</foreign>, of similar shape). The lay-out of the page is in columns for the <foreign xml:lang="ta">mūlam</foreign>.</p>
                  </summary>
                  
                  
